dubstep.solution.expr

Class ExpressionRewrite

  • java.lang.Object
    • dubstep.solution.expr.ExpressionRewrite
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ExtractAggregates

    public abstract class ExpressionRewrite
extends java.lang.Object
    A use of the visitor pattern to rewrite expressions. Disassembles and re-assembles an arbitrary expression. This class does nothing by itself, but subclasses can overload individual methods to avoid having to re-code all of the recursion by themselves. Because the native visitor pattern does not allow values to be returned, values are returned indirectly through the ret() and get() methods. Each visitor method is expected to call ret() to return a value.
